1. cs.DS (Discrete Mathematics): The paper deals with the formalization of time-symmetry in the context of discrete dynamical systems, specifically cellular automata. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory): The concept of time-symmetry is related to the reversibility of physical processes, which is a topic of interest in information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the properties and relations of time-symmetric cellular automata, which can be seen as a type of dynamical system. 
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The study of cellular automata and their properties is a topic of interest in computational complexity theory. 
5. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The formalization of time-symmetry in cellular automata involves the use of logical reasoning and mathematical proofs.
